OL,3,CHinckley mum says scrapping two-child
OL,4,Cbenefit cap will 'change her life'
OL,6,FThe policy which was introduced by
OL,7,Fformer Conservative Chancellor George
OL,8,FOsborne, means parents can only claim
OL,9,FUniversal Credit or tax credits for
OL,10,Ftheir first two children.
OL,12,FIt applies to third or subsequent
OL,13,Fchildren born after 6 April 2016.
OL,15,FThe Conservatives introduced the
OL,16,Fpolicy in an effort to incentivise out-
OL,17,Fof-work parents into employment,
OL,18,Farguing people on benefits "should
OL,19,Fface the same financial choices about
OL,20,Fhaving children as those supporting
OL,21,Fthemselves solely through work".
